<div class="delegate">
  <h3 class="do_it">Delegate this task to someone else who can do it</h3>
  <br>
  If you can, delegate it right now!
  <br>
  <br>
  Then, if you will need to follow-up if it isn't done, add it to your checklist of items you are waiting on.
  <br>
  <button class="button <%=@mode%>" type="button"><%= link_to "Add to 'Waiting On' Checklist", develop_inbox_path(@inbox, item: item, next_step: "waiting") %></button>
  <br>
  <br>
  If it doesn't need follow-up, you can move on.
  <br>
  <button class="button <%=@mode%>" type="button"><%= link_to "Delete Item", develop_inbox_path(@inbox, item: item, next_step: "delete"), data: { confirm: "Confirm deletion?" } %></button>
  <button class="button <%=@mode%>"x type="button"><%= link_to "Go to Next Item (without Deleting)", develop_inbox_path(@inbox, item: item, next_step: "next") %></button>
  <br>
  <br>
  If delegating can't happen right now, the action of delegating should become a task (single step) or a project (multi-step) to address it later.
  <br>
  <button class="button <%=@mode%>" type="button"><%= link_to "Add a Task", develop_inbox_path(@inbox, item: item, next_step: "add_single") %></button>
  <button class="button <%=@mode%>" type="button"><%= link_to "Start a new Project", develop_inbox_path(@inbox, item: item, next_step: "start_project") %></button>
</div>
